And there's a lot of money depending
on this next putt, folks.

467
01:00:12,440 --> 01:00:13,953
A lot of money.

468
01:00:14,120 --> 01:00:19,069
Now the crowd is all settled.
No one is even breathing.

469
01:00:21,160 --> 01:00:22,957
He's lining up the putt.

470
01:00:27,200 --> 01:00:29,395
He sets himself.

471
01:00:29,560 --> 01:00:32,916
And ladies and gentlemen,
here is the big one.

472
01:00:56,480 --> 01:00:59,677
- Hi, Bob.
- Hi, Hal. You're a little late.

473
01:00:59,840 --> 01:01:03,674
Yeah, I had a big date.
Just me, the chick and the full moon.

474
01:01:03,840 --> 01:01:06,877
- Now you hit me where I live.
- You mean the chick?

475
01:01:07,040 --> 01:01:11,352
No, no, the full moon. You know
how I am about that astronomy jazz.

476
01:01:11,520 --> 01:01:15,479
An old Greek astronomer said that
when the man in the moon is smiling,

477
01:01:15,640 --> 01:01:18,313
all the stars and planets
are swinging.

478
01:01:18,480 --> 01:01:22,268
Mercury warms up a little bit more.
Jupiter starts jumping.

479
01:01:22,440 --> 01:01:25,113
Venus puts on a new hairdo
or manicure.

480
01:01:25,280 --> 01:01:29,512
All the stars and planets are having
a great, big party up there in the sky.

481
01:02:06,520 --> 01:02:10,069
<i>Sylvia, get up. The sun is shining
and it's a beautiful day.</i>

482
01:02:10,240 --> 01:02:12,800
<i>Are you crazy?
It's 3.30 in the morning.</i>

483
01:02:12,960 --> 01:02:17,829
<i>For the money it's costing, we'll
take the sun whenever they give it to us.</i>

484
01:02:30,760 --> 01:02:33,877
Stanley, Mr Novak wants to see you,
on the double.

485
01:02:36,240 --> 01:02:40,392
Check on that shipment. And send
that wire to New York. It's important.

486
01:02:41,400 --> 01:02:42,719
Hello?

487
01:02:42,880 --> 01:02:46,190
Oh, the senator. Senator Tyson.
Yes, put him on.

488
01:02:46,360 --> 01:02:47,713
Just a moment.

489
01:02:47,880 --> 01:02:52,795
Go to the airport. The captain of
the National Airlines jet just flew in.

490
01:02:52,960 --> 01:02:56,350
He left his briefcase in the cockpit
of the plane. Go and get it.

491
01:02:56,520 --> 01:02:59,876
It's at Gate 39.
Hurry up. Go on, go on.

492
01:03:00,800 --> 01:03:02,916
Hello, Senator. How are you?

493
01:03:41,000 --> 01:03:45,278
<i>Last call for passengers, Flight 104
for Chicago and Los Angeles.</i>

494
01:03:45,440 --> 01:03:47,317
<i>Now loading Gate 5.</i>

495
01:04:04,000 --> 01:04:08,118
<i>Last call for passengers, Flight 104
for Chicago and Los Angeles.</i>

496
01:04:08,280 --> 01:04:11,078
<i>Now loading Gate 5. Last call.</i>

497
01:04:33,440 --> 01:04:36,238
We are sorry
we cannot accommodate you

498
01:04:36,400 --> 01:04:40,473
but shall be happy to be of service
in the future. Cordially yours...

499
01:04:42,120 --> 01:04:46,272
Hello? Yes, this is Mr Novak.

500
01:04:46,440 --> 01:04:48,351
Yes.

501
01:04:48,520 --> 01:04:53,674
Sorry, we have 3,000 employees.
I couldn't know every one of them.

502
01:04:55,040 --> 01:04:57,270
Oh, Stanley? Yes, he works for me.

503
01:05:00,800 --> 01:05:02,153
He what?

504
01:06:27,480 --> 01:06:30,631
I just saw one man on the floor.
Where is everybody?

505
01:06:30,800 --> 01:06:34,998
They're inside having a meeting at
the round table. Looks like trouble.

506
01:06:35,160 --> 01:06:38,550
I say one thing.
Striking is a matter of principle.

507
01:06:38,720 --> 01:06:40,631
Then let the principles strike.

508
01:06:40,800 --> 01:06:43,189
The seating at separate tables,
no fraternisation.

509
01:06:43,360 --> 01:06:45,954
And the bell captain
and his storm-trooper tactics.

510
01:06:46,120 --> 01:06:49,032
What we do after work is our business,
not theirs.

511
01:06:49,200 --> 01:06:53,159
You're right. They shouldn't tell us to stay
out of strip joints. I like strippers.

512
01:06:53,320 --> 01:06:57,029
Remember, fellas,
the decision must be made now.

513
01:07:11,520 --> 01:07:15,479
A-ha! So you're the ringleader.
I've caught you at last.

514
01:07:15,640 --> 01:07:18,791
I thought you were
a nice, quiet young man,

515
01:07:18,960 --> 01:07:21,394
and I find you're just a troublemaker.

516
01:07:21,560 --> 01:07:25,269
This is how you treat me.
You ought to be ashamed of yourself.

517
01:07:25,440 --> 01:07:29,797
I've given you a home away from home.
Yes, I have, you know I have.

518
01:07:29,960 --> 01:07:32,155
And this is the way you repay me.

519
01:07:32,320 --> 01:07:34,595
You're nothing but a strike creator.

520
01:07:34,760 --> 01:07:36,478
Yes, a troublemaker,

521
01:07:36,640 --> 01:07:39,757
an instigator, a picket-plugger,
yes, you are.

522
01:07:39,920 --> 01:07:44,232
Stop shaking your head. What's
the matter with you? Can't you talk?

523
01:07:48,120 --> 01:07:53,114
Certainly I can talk. I suspect I can talk
as well as any other man, Mr Novak.

524
01:07:54,120 --> 01:07:59,069
In that case...how is it we never
heard you talk before?

525
01:08:01,920 --> 01:08:04,070
Because no one ever asked me.

526
01:08:16,800 --> 01:08:19,758
<i>So you see? There was no story.</i>

527
01:08:19,920 --> 01:08:23,595
<i>But there is a moral,
and a simple one.</i>

528
01:08:23,760 --> 01:08:28,675
<i>You'll never know the next guy's
story... unless you ask.</i>

